===Etymology===
Uncertain. One popular theory derives the name from Malayalam ''kera'' (coconut tree) and ''alam'' (land), thus "land of coconuts", which is also the state's nickname.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|en|/ˈkɛɹələ/}}

